{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"351c3c5c-22d1-424f-be07-57898c8cb9a8","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2**, which supports the modern approach. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncInitialization, IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    // TestContext is injected via constructor in MSTest 3.8+\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; }\n\n    private HttpClient _client;\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        // Synchronous init\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        _client = new HttpClient();\n    }\n\n    // IAsyncInitialization — runs after constructor\n    public async Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        // Async init (e.g., seed a database, warm up a service)\n        await _client.GetAsync(\"https://example.com/health\");\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SyncTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(TestContext);\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task AsyncTest()\n    {\n        var response = await _client.GetAsync(\"https://example.com\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(response.IsSuccessStatusCode);\n    }\n\n    // IAsyncDisposable for cleanup\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync()\n    {\n        _client.Dispose();\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points (MSTest 3.x):**\n\n- **Constructor injection** of `TestContext` replaces the old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern.\n- **`IAsyncInitialization`** — implement `InitializeAsync()` for async setup that runs after the constructor but before each test.\n- **`IAsyncDisposable`** / `IDisposable` — preferred over `[TestCleanup]` for teardown.\n- You can still use `[ClassInitialize]` / `[AssemblyInitialize]` for one-time static setup if needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"781182de-3138-450b-aed8-5e5ef2eff971","outputTokens":479,"requestId":"A02E:350962:19A84E8:1D0CAE4:69FE8EC4"},"id":"9eaeed3f-daca-4f40-8cdb-a0fa11bb76a2","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:33:02.386Z","parentId":"fd6e6509-3170-4275-999f-4fee437b3144"}
